- How you doing?

00:10.927 --> 00:12.679
- Oh, hanging out.

00:12.762 --> 00:16.140
God, getting ready for
the Arkansas football season.

00:16.224 --> 00:19.853
-<i> In 2015, as part of</i>
<i>a "Nathan for You" DVD release,</i>

00:19.936 --> 00:21.563
<i>Comedy Central asked me</i>

00:21.646 --> 00:23.314
<i>to record</i>
<i>an audio commentary track</i>

00:23.398 --> 00:25.358
<i>for some of</i>
<i>my favorite episodes.</i>

00:25.442 --> 00:28.403
<i>In one segment, I helped</i>
<i>a struggling souvenir shop</i>

00:28.486 --> 00:30.447
<i>and in the process</i>

00:30.530 --> 00:32.949
<i>met a professional Bill Gates</i>
<i>impersonator named Bill Heath.</i>

00:33.032 --> 00:36.494
- When we started
our computers...

00:37.996 --> 00:40.039
back in the '80s,

00:40.123 --> 00:41.958
it was huge--

00:42.041 --> 00:45.295
in the business,
they were huge machines.

00:45.378 --> 00:47.422
-<i> I found him to be</i>
<i>a really interesting person,</i>

00:47.505 --> 00:49.257
<i>so when it came time</i>
<i>to record the commentary</i>

00:49.340 --> 00:52.302
<i>for his episode,</i>
<i>I invited him to join us</i>

00:52.385 --> 00:55.388
<i>and share his favorite memories</i>
<i>from making the show.</i>

00:55.472 --> 00:58.391
- Yeah, the owner
of the shop,

00:58.475 --> 01:00.059
I came in--
I was explaining to him

01:00.143 --> 01:03.980
about how the computers
were founded

01:04.063 --> 01:05.940
when we founded them
and so forth.

01:06.024 --> 01:07.066
-<i> But during</i>
<i>the recording</i>

01:07.150 --> 01:10.153
<i>Bill's attention</i>
<i>seemed scattered.</i>

01:10.236 --> 01:13.531
<i>He not only took a seven-minute</i>
<i>call from his phone company...</i>

01:13.615 --> 01:14.824
Right, people were posting
about the event on Twitter.

01:14.908 --> 01:18.453
- Yes, I want to
lower the rate.

01:18.536 --> 01:19.496
How long
will it be?

01:19.579 --> 01:21.122
- William, who is--
who is on the phone?

01:21.206 --> 01:23.833
- AT&amp;T.
Yeah, what's your number?

01:23.917 --> 01:25.043
I'm gonna call you back
on this promotion.

01:25.126 --> 01:27.378
<i>- But he also</i>
<i>went into detail</i>

01:27.462 --> 01:29.798
<i>about a long-lost love</i>
<i>from his past,</i>

01:29.881 --> 01:32.008
<i>a woman named</i>
<i>Frances Gaddy.</i>

01:32.091 --> 01:34.344
- I should have married her,
everybody interfered.

01:34.427 --> 01:35.887
- Who interfered?

01:35.970 --> 01:38.223
- Oh, my mother, you know,
a lot of friends.

01:38.306 --> 01:40.225
They--they--you know, mothers,
a lot of mothers

01:40.308 --> 01:43.102
have picked out the girl
they want you to marry.

01:43.186 --> 01:46.689
Well, it doesn't work
that way.

01:46.773 --> 01:49.234
{\an3}- Is that a regret
of yours?

01:49.317 --> 01:51.694
- It's one of 'em, yeah,
I look back.

01:51.778 --> 01:54.739
I should have
married her.

01:54.823 --> 01:56.533
[sighs]

01:56.616 --> 01:58.159
I don't know
where she is now.

01:58.243 --> 01:59.410
I've been trying
to find her.

01:59.494 --> 02:00.995
-<i> I didn't think much of it</i>
<i>at the time,</i>

02:01.079 --> 02:03.623
<i>but as the months</i>
<i>went on,</i>

02:03.706 --> 02:05.708
<i>Bill began to show up</i>
<i>at the office unannounced</i>

02:05.792 --> 02:06.918
<i>to deliver gifts...</i>

02:07.001 --> 02:08.211
- Oh, it's
a serving set.

02:08.294 --> 02:09.294
{\an3}- Yeah.

02:09.378 --> 02:10.588
<i>- Grab a quick snack,</i>

02:10.672 --> 02:12.507
<i>or just to hang out,</i>

02:12.590 --> 02:14.759
<i>and the name Frances Gaddy</i>
<i>kept coming up.</i>

02:21.057 --> 02:23.226
<i>Thoughts of this failed romance</i>
<i>from over 50 years ago</i>

02:23.309 --> 02:25.979
<i>seemed to completely</i>
<i>consume him.</i>

02:27.981 --> 02:30.525
{\an1}Frances?
I don't know.

02:30.608 --> 02:31.442
{\an1}Can I use the
bathroom quickly,

02:31.526 --> 02:32.902
{\an1}and then we'll talk
when I come out?

02:32.986 --> 02:34.737
- Sure.
- Okay.

02:34.821 --> 02:36.948
<i>And in getting to know him,</i>
<i>I began to understand why.</i>

02:37.031 --> 02:38.491
<i>At the age of 78,</i>

02:38.575 --> 02:41.035
<i>Bill lived alone</i>
<i>and had never married.</i>

02:41.119 --> 02:44.497
<i>His closest bond was with</i>
<i>his alma mater's football team,</i>

02:44.581 --> 02:45.999
<i>the Arkansas Razorbacks.</i>

02:46.082 --> 02:48.918
- Each year
I give $3,000 total

02:49.002 --> 02:53.256
for the Arkansas Razorbacks
athletic programs.

02:53.339 --> 02:56.092
Whoo, pig sooie!

02:56.175 --> 02:58.761
Razorbacks!
Number one.

02:58.845 --> 03:01.764
-<i> His lifestyle was modest</i>
<i>and very organized.</i>

03:01.848 --> 03:04.017
- This is a stack of
loan offers.

03:04.100 --> 03:08.021
RISE preapproved
for $2,600.

03:08.104 --> 03:12.108
Here's the same
RISE for $5,000.

03:12.191 --> 03:16.779
$1,000 prequalified,
in your account, $2,500.

03:16.863 --> 03:19.782
-<i> With such meticulous record</i>
<i>keeping in his daily life,</i>

03:19.866 --> 03:23.036
<i>it was surprising that he had</i>
<i>no information about Frances</i>

03:23.119 --> 03:24.579
<i>other than her name.</i>

03:24.662 --> 03:25.538
{\an1}Have you looked for her?
I mean--

03:25.622 --> 03:29.709
{\an8}- I tried once
or twice, yeah.

03:29.792 --> 03:32.420
-<i> An exhaustive Internet search</i>
<i>turned up nothing.</i>

03:32.503 --> 03:34.464
<i>If she had married someone,</i>

03:34.547 --> 03:36.507
<i>it was likely she'd have</i>
<i>a different last name.</i>

03:36.591 --> 03:39.218
<i>And that meant with over</i>
<i>600,000 women named Frances</i>

03:39.302 --> 03:41.512
<i>currently living</i>
<i>in the U.S.,</i>

03:41.596 --> 03:45.141
<i>the task of finding</i>
<i>the one Bill was looking for</i>

03:45.224 --> 03:47.810
<i>would take an incredible amount</i>
<i>of time and effort.</i>

03:47.894 --> 03:49.854
<i>But the challenge of solving</i>
<i>a near-impossible mystery</i>

03:49.938 --> 03:52.357
<i>intrigued me.</i>

03:52.440 --> 03:54.651
<i>Plus, there was something</i>
<i>about an old man</i>

03:54.734 --> 03:56.527
<i>so filled with regret that was</i>
<i>hard for me to ignore,</i>

03:56.611 --> 04:00.823
<i>and I realized</i>
<i>if I didn't help him do this,</i>

04:00.907 --> 04:02.617
<i>no one would.</i>

04:03.785 --> 04:06.746
<i>[somber music]</i>

04:06.829 --> 04:14.754
♪ ♪

04:18.632 --> 04:21.970
<i>It was becoming clear</i>
<i>that finding this woman</i>

04:22.053 --> 04:24.639
<i>would take a lot more effort</i>
<i>than a Google search.</i>

04:24.722 --> 04:26.557
<i>But before devoting</i>
<i>my time to this,</i>

04:26.641 --> 04:29.394
<i>I wanted to see what</i>
<i>Bill's motivations were.</i>

04:29.477 --> 04:32.271
- Oh, I need to confess
a lot of things to her

04:32.355 --> 04:36.192
about what--
between the time we--

04:36.275 --> 04:38.903
the lapse of time
and fill in the gaps,

04:38.987 --> 04:42.657
her gaps
and my gaps,

04:42.740 --> 04:44.158
to put the puzzle
together.

04:44.242 --> 04:48.454
- I mean, a best-case scenario,
what do you hope will happen?

04:48.538 --> 04:49.664
- Well, I hope
I can find her.

04:49.747 --> 04:51.249
- And then what?
What happens when you find her?

04:51.332 --> 04:53.126
- Well, I'll go
from there.

04:53.209 --> 04:56.462
- Well, what does
that mean?

04:56.546 --> 04:58.131
- Well, if she's
married,

04:58.214 --> 05:01.634
you have to accept it
that way.

05:01.718 --> 05:02.969
- But if she's not?

05:03.052 --> 05:06.305
- If she's not, well,
maybe we could get married...

05:06.389 --> 05:07.890
[laughs]

05:07.974 --> 05:10.810
Finally.

05:10.893 --> 05:11.853
- You still love her?

05:11.936 --> 05:14.647
- Yeah, I do.

05:14.731 --> 05:17.984
-<i> I was moved by how</i>
<i>romantic of a tale this was.</i>

05:18.067 --> 05:20.778
- Love is hard to come by,
you know.

05:20.862 --> 05:22.572
-<i> The possibility of</i>
<i>reuniting Bill</i>

05:22.655 --> 05:24.532
<i>with his long-lost love</i>
<i>was so cool.</i>

05:24.615 --> 05:27.744
<i>So I told him</i>
<i>I had some good news.</i>

05:27.827 --> 05:30.872
I want to use the resources
of my show

05:30.955 --> 05:32.999
to help you
find Frances.

05:33.082 --> 05:36.252
- Well, that's--

05:38.129 --> 05:41.257
I think that's a true friend
that would do that.

05:41.340 --> 05:43.885
-<i> But Bill hadn't seen</i>
<i>or spoken to Frances</i>

05:43.968 --> 05:45.762
<i>in over 50 years,</i>

05:45.845 --> 05:47.889
<i>leaving us with</i>
<i>very little to go on.</i>

05:47.972 --> 05:49.307
- You know, she married
on the rebound,

05:49.390 --> 05:52.727
unhappy marriage,
she got a divorce,

05:52.810 --> 05:55.813
and I think she got another
divorce, I don't know.

05:55.897 --> 05:57.607
- So wait,
who did she marry?

05:57.690 --> 06:00.693
- Charles something.
I don't remember his last name.

06:00.777 --> 06:01.611
{\an3}- She married
a Charles.

06:01.694 --> 06:03.154
- Yes.

06:03.237 --> 06:04.447
- But she could be
married again?

06:04.530 --> 06:06.032
- She could be.
- You just don't know.

06:06.115 --> 06:07.492
- I don't know.

06:07.575 --> 06:09.285
-<i> The only thing</i>
<i>he did know for sure</i>

06:09.368 --> 06:11.162
<i>was her name</i>
<i>before she was married</i>

06:11.245 --> 06:12.955
<i>and what she looked like</i>
<i>in 1961.</i>

06:13.039 --> 06:15.666
{\an1}- Brown hair,
brown eyes.

06:15.750 --> 06:18.377
-<i> With no photos and just</i>
<i>a sketch of Frances</i>

06:18.461 --> 06:20.755
<i>that Bill did</i>
<i>from memory...</i>

06:20.838 --> 06:24.300
So this is the woman
we're looking for?

06:24.383 --> 06:26.636
♪ ♪

06:26.719 --> 06:28.679
- Yes.

06:28.763 --> 06:30.348
-<i> it quickly</i>
<i>became clear</i>

06:30.431 --> 06:32.308
<i>this was going to be</i>
<i>an uphill battle.</i>

06:32.391 --> 06:35.728
<i>But Bill did recall one thing</i>
<i>that could be helpful.</i>

06:35.812 --> 06:38.231
- Last time I saw her was in
Little Rock in Arkansas.

06:38.314 --> 06:41.067
{\an1}I was working at
Moses Melody Shop,

06:41.150 --> 06:43.820
the music record store.

06:43.903 --> 06:45.822
-<i> I felt that if I could get</i>
<i>Bill back to the city</i>

06:45.905 --> 06:48.699
<i>where they first dated, it</i>
<i>might jog some of his memories.</i>

06:48.783 --> 06:52.787
<i>So I booked us a flight</i>
<i>to Little Rock, Arkansas,</i>

06:52.870 --> 06:55.498
<i>to begin our search</i>
<i>for Frances.</i>

06:55.581 --> 07:00.169
<i>[mid-tempo music]</i>

07:00.253 --> 07:01.087
<i>It had been some time</i>
<i>since Bill had been back</i>

07:01.170 --> 07:03.756
<i>in his home state,</i>

07:03.840 --> 07:05.716
<i>and he seemed enthusiastic</i>
<i>to return.</i>

07:05.800 --> 07:07.677
Are you excited, Bill?
- Yeah.

07:07.760 --> 07:11.472
{\an1}It's hometown, man.
I grew up here.

07:11.556 --> 07:12.723
-<i> And as I had hoped,</i>
<i>it wasn't long</i>

07:12.807 --> 07:15.434
<i>before old memories began</i>
<i>to come back.</i>

07:15.518 --> 07:17.937
{\an1}- God, Mother used to
pick me up right there,

07:18.020 --> 07:21.065
that station.

07:21.149 --> 07:22.567
{\an1}There was a plant
right there.

07:22.650 --> 07:25.820
Dr. Pepper Company
right there, man.

07:25.903 --> 07:28.406
{\an1}Now, that's the old
West Side Junior High.

07:28.489 --> 07:30.199
My uncle taught there.

07:30.283 --> 07:32.201
-<i> With Bill's past</i>
<i>fresh in his mind,</i>

07:32.285 --> 07:34.912
<i>we headed downtown</i>
<i>to Moses Melody Shop,</i>

07:34.996 --> 07:37.206
<i>the last place</i>
<i>Bill had seen Frances</i>

07:37.290 --> 07:38.708
<i>over 50 years ago.</i>

07:38.791 --> 07:40.293
{\an1}- It used to be right there,
the second building.

07:40.376 --> 07:43.045
{\an1}I don't think
it's there anymore.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.213
{\an1}Everything has
changed.

07:44.297 --> 07:46.215
-<i> Things had changed.</i>

07:46.299 --> 07:48.718
<i>Moses Melodies was now</i>
<i>a wig store,</i>

07:48.801 --> 07:50.386
<i>but once inside,</i>

07:50.469 --> 07:52.555
<i>memories of that final</i>
<i>encounter with Frances</i>

07:52.638 --> 07:53.556
<i>began to resurface.</i>

07:53.639 --> 07:56.559
{\an1}- Well, there was
a counter, like, here.

07:56.642 --> 08:00.396
{\an1}I was right here,
and she came in that way.

08:00.479 --> 08:02.940
{\an3}I was behind
the counter here.

08:03.024 --> 08:04.400
{\an1}- Okay.

08:04.483 --> 08:07.445
{\an3}- She brought
her tape recorder.

08:07.528 --> 08:08.821
That's the last
time I saw her.

08:08.905 --> 08:12.325
-<i> As he continued,</i>
<i>I began to understand</i>

08:12.408 --> 08:13.993
<i>what a loss this was</i>
<i>for him.</i>

08:14.076 --> 08:16.996
{\an1}- She cried, said,
"I'll love you to my grave."

08:17.079 --> 08:18.247
I never will
forget that.

08:18.331 --> 08:19.999
- That's what
she said to you?

08:20.082 --> 08:22.877
- Mm-hmm, that's
what she told me.

08:22.960 --> 08:24.170
{\an3}- So why'd you never
see her again?

08:24.253 --> 08:27.882
{\an1}- She said, "You want your
career." I headed to Hollywood.

08:27.965 --> 08:31.177
{\an1}She said,
"You want your career."

08:33.554 --> 08:35.722
{\an1}Those are the breaks.
[chuckles]

08:35.806 --> 08:37.767
-<i> I was starting</i>
<i>to realize</i>

08:37.850 --> 08:39.602
<i>why I was so drawn to</i>
<i>Bill's story.</i>

08:39.684 --> 08:43.272
<i>As someone who also left</i>
<i>a lot behind</i>

08:43.356 --> 08:44.607
<i>to pursue a career</i>
<i>in Hollywood,</i>

08:44.690 --> 08:48.152
<i>I couldn't help but feel</i>
<i>an odd kinship with him.</i>

08:48.236 --> 08:49.820
<i>But the fact</i>
<i>remained that</i>

08:49.904 --> 08:52.448
<i>we still had nothing concrete</i>
<i>to go off of</i>

08:52.531 --> 08:55.576
<i>besides a first name</i>
<i>and Bill's sketch.</i>

08:58.037 --> 08:59.288
{\an8}- Yeah.
- White?

08:59.372 --> 09:01.165
{\an8}- White.
- She's white.

09:01.249 --> 09:04.001
<i>It was as if we were trying to</i>
<i>find a missing person.</i>

09:05.086 --> 09:08.798
{\an8}This is a woman.

09:08.881 --> 09:10.758
<i>And it was hard to know</i>
<i>what would lead us to her</i>

09:10.841 --> 09:12.510
<i>or where to even begin.</i>

09:12.593 --> 09:15.054
<i>On the way back</i>
<i>to our hotel,</i>

09:15.137 --> 09:17.265
<i>Bill wanted to take me by</i>
<i>his old high school.</i>

09:17.348 --> 09:21.310
- Central High, the integration,
nine black students.

09:21.394 --> 09:23.020
{\an1}They had to get
the federal troops in here

09:23.104 --> 09:26.899
to enter them.

09:26.983 --> 09:28.025
{\an1}We always got along
with the blacks,

09:28.109 --> 09:31.362
no problem.

09:31.445 --> 09:33.698
{\an1}It's too bad that
it had to come to this,

09:33.781 --> 09:35.658
but it happened.

09:35.741 --> 09:36.450
-<i> It was neat to learn</i>
<i>a bit of the history</i>

09:36.534 --> 09:38.035
<i>of Bill's high school,</i>

09:38.119 --> 09:41.539
<i>but then something came up</i>
<i>that could be useful.</i>

09:41.622 --> 09:44.500
Did Frances go to
your high school?

09:44.583 --> 09:48.421
{\an1}- Um...

09:48.504 --> 09:51.048
{\an1}no, she went to
Dumas High School, I believe.

09:51.132 --> 09:55.428
Dumas, Arkansas.

09:55.511 --> 09:56.971
{\an3}- Dumas.

09:57.054 --> 09:59.056
<i>It turned out that Dumas</i>
<i>was a town</i>

09:59.140 --> 10:01.225
<i>just under two hours</i>
<i>from Little Rock,</i>

10:01.309 --> 10:03.352
<i>and if we could get in touch</i>
<i>with their high school,</i>

10:03.436 --> 10:05.438
<i>they'd most likely have</i>
<i>student records</i>

10:05.521 --> 10:08.149
<i>or even an old yearbook that</i>
<i>could give us a clue.</i>

10:08.232 --> 10:09.859
<i>But the school was closed</i>
<i>for the day</i>

10:09.942 --> 10:11.110
<i>so we'd have to call</i>
<i>in the morning.</i>

10:11.193 --> 10:13.529
<i>In the meantime,</i>
<i>we checked into our hotel</i>

10:13.612 --> 10:15.573
<i>in downtown Little Rock,</i>

10:15.656 --> 10:18.075
<i>and after getting unpacked</i>
<i>and grabbing some dinner,</i>

10:18.159 --> 10:21.579
<i>we decided to</i>
<i>call it a night.</i>

10:21.662 --> 10:25.499
[cell phone chimes off]

10:25.583 --> 10:27.710
This is kind of
a fun trip, huh?

10:27.793 --> 10:28.252
- Yeah.

10:28.336 --> 10:30.629
- Just the boys.

10:30.713 --> 10:33.257
- Mm-hmm.

10:33.341 --> 10:35.217
- Can I ask you
something?

10:35.301 --> 10:37.094
- Yes.

10:37.178 --> 10:39.680
- What's your favorite memory
of Frances?

10:46.854 --> 10:51.359
- Probably when we were
on the bed there together.

10:51.442 --> 10:52.735
- When you were
on the bed together?

10:52.818 --> 10:54.028
- Yeah.

